The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Metro trains ran up to 20 minutes late from 5pm to 6pm on Monday because of a snag at the crossover point of New Garia (Kavi Subhas) station. According to Metro officials, the crossover time, usually two minutes, stretched to eight minutes on Monday afternoon.  East-West Metro: The Centre has asked the state to take up the issue of the slow progress of the East-West Metro Railway project with the Union urban development department.   SSKM beds: SSKM hospital will have 25 more Intensive Therapy Unit (ITU) beds soon, Pradip Mitra, director, Institute of Post Graduate Medicine and Research, said on Monday. The ITU unit currently has five beds.  Arrested: Cops from Mumbai arrested Kalyan Banerjee, who had allegedly duped several people in the Maharashtra capital, in an apartment near Anandapur, off the EM Bypass, on Saturday. Banerjee, who lived in Mumbais Andheri, fled to Calcutta after collecting Rs 14 lakh from several people promising them amenities like water and gas connections, said a cop.  Man dead: Francis Antony, a 30-year-old resident of Marquis Lane, died after a lorry carrying idols for immersion, hit the scooter he was riding on Sarat Bose Road on Sunday.                                                                                                                                               
